        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 5:52PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 552 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Texas Creek, or 51 miles west of Pueblo, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hillside.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
